&lt;p&gt;I am a PhD researcher focused on scalable distributed systems, consistency models, and fault-tolerant coordination. My work explores the design of scalable consensus and replication mechanisms, with applications to sharded and large-scale distributed systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My broader research interests lie in scalable runtime systems and resilient execution environments for large-scale computing. This includes task scheduling, checkpointing, fault-tolerant coordination mechanisms, and runtime infrastructure for heterogeneous and distributed computing systems.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>